String Method:
1)String Length
The length property returns the length of a string.
2)Finding a String in a String
The indexOf() method returns the index of (the position of) the first occurrence of a specified text in a string.
3)Extracting String Parts

There are 3 methods for extracting a part of a string:
slice(start, end)
substring(start, end)
substr(start, length)

a)The slice() Method / substring()
slice() extracts a part of a string and returns the extracted part in a new string.

The method takes 2 parameters: the starting index (position), and the ending index (position).


4)Converting to Upper and Lower Case
var text2 = text1.toUpperCase();
var text2 = text1.toLowerCase();


5)CharAt(index) : used to get char at the particulat index



JavaScript Math Object

1)Math.round()
Math.round(x) returns the value of x rounded to its nearest integer
Math.round(4.7);    // 5
Math.round(4.4);    // 4

2)Math.pow()
Math.pow(x, y) returns the value of x to the power of y.
Math.pow(8, 2);      // 64

3)Math.ceil()
Math.ceil(x) returns the value of x rounded up to its nearest integer:
Math.ceil(4.4);     // 5

4)Math.floor()
Math.floor(x) returns the value of x rounded down to its nearest integer.
Math.floor(4.7);


Array :
JavaScript arrays are used to store multiple values in a single variable.
var array_name = [item1, item2, ...]; 

- Access the Elements of an Array
You refer to an array element by referring to the index number.
var name = cars[0];

- Javascript array's are heterogeneous.

-Array Properties and methods
-Looping Array element
-Adding Array element  : arrayName.push();
-Removing Array element : arrayName.pop();


var arr = new Array(40, 100, 1, 5, 25, 10); // Bad
var arr1 = [40, 100, 1, 5, 25, 10];          // Good